sec.p:
Additionally, a survey using the International Classification of Functioning, Disability, and Health (ICF) was conducted among the operated soldiers to assess the early rehabilitation process and their ability to perform daily and professional activities. The survey focused on the following criteria:
Patient verticalization postsurgery (domain d410, changing body position);
Walking ability and distance postsurgery (domain d450, walking and moving);
Ability and duration of sitting postsurgery (domain d4153, sitting position);
Activity limitations (restricted movements and actions) (domain d430-d449, moving, handling objects, d9201, sports activities).
